{"type":"message","id":"8f8fa790","parentId":"2180c882","timestamp":"2026-05-21T20:00:45.835Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"8f3ad0de-91da-4626-9989-e7c45612bce1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"err-err-7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"title\": \"[Investigate] Task Dispatcher: session file changed while embedded prompt lock was released: /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/076895dd-43e4-428f-ae33-ec91ab0df26a.jsonl\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Auto-created from Scheduler Error Feed.\\nCron job: Task Dispatcher (7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f)\\nError: EmbeddedAttemptSessionTakeoverError: session file changed while embedded prompt lock was released: /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/076895dd-43e4-428f-ae33-ec91ab0df26a.jsonl\\nConsecutive errors: 5\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T14:12:34.337Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-created from error feed for Task Dispatcher\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T16:35:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog \\u2014 Task Dispatcher cron self-error (session takeover, 5 consecutive). This is an OpenClaw infrastructure issue, not investigable by agents. Needs OpenClaw update or cron config change. Resetting to reduce noise.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T17:25:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Cron healthy, marking done\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"errorId\": \"err-7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"jobId\": \"7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-21T17:25:00.000Z\",\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-21T17:25:00.000Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"summary\": \"Resolved \\u2014 Task Dispatcher cron is healthy (status: ok). Session takeover errors were transient. No further action needed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"err-err-dae7406b-ec78-4752-ba93-91bc62541f7d\",\n    \"title\": \"[Investigate] Daily Station Check: cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Auto-created from Scheduler Error Feed.\\nCron job: Daily Station Check (dae7406b-ec78-4752-ba93-91bc62541f7d)\\nError: cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)\\nConsecutive errors: 1\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-20T11:28:13.917Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-created from error feed for Daily Station Check\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T13:30:35.812Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from in_progress to backlog\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T13:40:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"dispatcher\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress by Task Dispatcher\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T16:35:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog \\u2014 task stale for ~3h with no progress update. Will be re-picked up by dispatcher or main session.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T17:25:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Cron healthy, marking done\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"errorId\": \"err-dae7406b-ec78-4752-ba93-91bc62541f7d\",\n    \"jobId\": \"dae7406b-ec78-4752-ba93-91bc62541f7d\",\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-21T17:25:00.000Z\",\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-05-21T13:40:00.000Z\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-21T17:25:00.000Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"summary\": \"Resolved \\u2014 Daily Station Check cron is healthy (status: ok). Timeout was transient. No further action needed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-mp7d3s9w-1lmf\",\n    \"title\": \"Task Completion \\u2014 summary and visibility improvement.\",\n    \"assignee\": \"archivist\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Task Completion \\u2014 summary and visibility improvement.\\n\\nThe auto-move from In Progress to Done works well. But when a task \\nmoves to Done, I can't tell WHAT was actually done. The card just \\nsays \\\"Done\\\" with no context.\\n\\nFix:\\n\\n1. When a task completes and auto-moves to Done, the card must \\n   include a brief summary of what was accomplished. This summary \\n   should be:\\n   - Written by the agent that completed the task\\n   - 1-3 sentences describing the actual outcome\\n   - Stored on the task card itself, visible in the Kanban view\\n   - Also visible when I click \\\"More Details\\\" on the card\\n\\n2. The \\\"More Details\\\" view on any Done card should show:\\n   - Original task description\\n   - Completion summary (what was actually done)\\n   - Which agent completed it\\n   - Timestamp of completion\\n   - Any relevant links or artifacts produced (files changed, \\n     commits made, etc.)\\n\\n3. In the Kanban view, a Done card should show at minimum:\\n   - Task title\\n   - One-line completion summary (truncated if needed)\\n   - \\\"Done by [Agent] \\u2022 [time]\\\"\\n\\n4. If the task was created manually by me (not auto-generated from \\n   an error or cron job), the agent who picks it up should write \\n   the completion summary before moving it to Done. If no summary \\n   is written, the task should NOT auto-move \\u2014 it should stay In \\n   Progress with a flag: \\\"Awaiting completion summary.\\\"\\n\\nThis applies to ALL tasks going forward. Retroactively fixing old \\nDone tasks is optional \\u2014 only if quick.\\n\\nReport your approach before implementing.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T20:20:43.364Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Task created\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T20:20:45.084Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T20:36:50.973Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from done to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T15:52:14.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"moved\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Moved from in_progress to backlog \\u2014 task stale since 2026-05-15T20:41:07.666Z, no active work\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T16:03:49.827Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to done\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-18T23:58:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"dispatcher\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress by Task Dispatcher\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:19.316Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from in_progress to done\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:19.316Z\",\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-05-18T23:58:00.000Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:19.316Z\",\n    \"summary\": \"Completed by archivist. Last action: started \\u2014 Status changed from done to in_progress\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"err-err-7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"title\": \"[Investigate] Task Dispatcher: cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Auto-created from Scheduler Error Feed.\\nCron job: Task Dispatcher (7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f)\\nError: cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)\\nConsecutive errors: 1\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-18T14:21:02.512Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-created from error feed for Task Dispatcher\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:18.581Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from in_progress to done\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"errorId\": \"err-7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"jobId\": \"7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:18.581Z\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:18.581Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"summary\": \"Completed by monkey.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-mp8p7in6-33ju\",\n    \"title\": \"Dashboard Animation\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:17.644Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"note\": \"The living office animations aren't rendering despite being deployed. \\nI need this area to be alive \\u2014 imagine a fish tank. The station is the \\ntank, the agents are the fish, tasks are the food. Fish don't sit still \\nin stagnant water. They swim, drift, feed, interact. The tank is always \\nalive even when nothing's happening.\\n\\nIf the current approach works, fix it. If it doesn't, rebuild it.\\n\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\nPHASE 1: DIAGNOSTIC\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\n\\nAnswer with evidence, not assumptions:\\n\\n1. How are sprites rendered? Canvas? DOM <img> tags? SVG? React components?\\n   Paste the relevant 20 lines from StationRoom.tsx.\\n\\n2. How are animations applied? CSS keyframes? Framer Motion? \\n   requestAnimationFrame? Canvas draw loop?\\n\\n3. Open browser DevTools (F12) \\u2192 Elements \\u2192 find a sprite element.\\n   - Does it have animation/transition/transform CSS properties?\\n   - Console tab: any JavaScript errors?\\n   - Network tab: are the CSS files loading? Search for \\\"sprite-working\\\" \\n     or \\\"ambient-pulse\\\" in loaded stylesheets.\\n\\n4. What data is reaching StationRoom? Console.log agent name, status, \\n   currentAction. Are values changing or stuck?\\n\\n5. Are the CSS classes (sprite-working, sprite-sleeping, ambient-pulse, \\n   ambient-flicker) actually on the DOM elements? Do the CSS rules exist?\\n\\nReport findings before making changes.\\n\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\nPHASE 2: IF CSS ANIMATIONS WORK \\u2014 FIX THE BUG\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\n\\nIf the diagnostic shows animations are present but not firing:\\n- Fix whatever's blocking them (missing class application, data not \\n  updating, SSR vs client mismatch)\\n- Force a visible test: Space Monkey with green \\\"TEST\\\" bubble, \\n  Systems Engineer walking across the floorplan\\n- Verify in browser DevTools that animation properties are active\\n\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\nPHASE 3: IF CSS ANIMATIONS DON'T WORK \\u2014 CANVAS FISH TANK\\n\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\u2550\\n\\nIf CSS animations are fundamentally unreliable, rebuild using a single \\nHTML5 Canvas with a requestAnimationFrame loop \\u2014 like an actual fish \\ntank simulation.\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n- One full-size Canvas element fills the Spacestation area\\n- Room backgrounds drawn once as a static layer\\n- Agent sprites drawn on top as an animated layer\\n- Single requestAnimationFrame loop at 60fps:\\\n\n⚠️ [... middle content omitted — showing head and tail ...]\n\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-105\",\n    \"title\": \"Fix task persistence \\u2014 saveTasks not writing to disk\",\n    \"assignee\": \"engineer\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n    \"note\": \"Fixed with direct fetch API to /api/save-tasks endpoint\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-106\",\n    \"title\": \"